text.section:
On receipt of a notification request form under § 11-104(f)(1) or (g) of this title or a written request from a witness for notification, a commitment unit, if practicable, shall notify the victim, victim's representative, or witness of:
receipt of the notification request form;
the date when the defendant or child respondent was placed in the custody of the commitment unit;
how to change the address to receive notice for the victim, victim's representative, witness, or the person to receive notice for the victim; and
how to elect not to receive future notices.

The commitment unit shall notify a victim, victim's representative, or witness, in advance if practicable, if any of the following events occur concerning the defendant or child respondent:
an escape;
a recapture;
a transfer to another commitment unit;
a release from confinement and any conditions attached to the release; and
the death of the defendant or child respondent.
